Salesforce Release Notes
New and Changed Standard Platform Events

Receive real-time notifications from Salesforce by subscribing to the channels of these new and changed standard platform events.

Mobile
Store data about users' email activity in a Salesforce mobile app with Enhanced Mobile App Security
Use the new MobileEmailEventStore object, which corresponds to the MobileEmailEvent platform event. Introduced in API version 48.0.
Store data about Enhanced Mobile App Security policy events in a Salesforce mobile app with Enhanced Mobile App Security
Use the new MobileEnfPolicyEventStore object, which stores data for MobileEnforcedPolicyEvent. Introduced in API version 48.0.
Store data about users' screenshots in a Salesforce mobile app with Enhanced Mobile App Security
Use the new MobileScreenshotEventStore object, which stores data for MobileScreenshotEvent. Introduced in API version 48.0.
Store data about users' phone calls and text messages in a Salesforce mobile app with Enhanced Mobile App Security
Use the new MobileTelephonyEventStore object, which stores data for MobileTelephonyEvent. Introduced in API version 48.0.

Security, Identity, and Privacy

Track the origin IP address for logins with multiple proxies
Use the new ForwardedForIp field on LoginEvent and LoginEventStream.
Identify the Experience Cloud site related to an insecure external asset
Use the new NETWORK_ID field on the Insecure External Assets event type.
Determine the CSP HTTP header that identified an insecure external asset
Use the new DISPOSITION field on the Insecure External Assets event type.
View the message for the error blocking the download request, if any.
Use the new DOWNLOAD_ERROR field on the Wave Download event type.
